                <head>364. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 6, 1968, the EC Commission approved an increase in the supplementary
                    levy on turkey legs and thighs from third countries from $0.3125 to $0.375 per
                    kilogram, effective February 10. On September 4, the Commission further revised
                    its supplementary levies on poultry imports, eliminating those on whole chickens
                    and chicken halves and <pb facs="0891" n="857" xml:id="pg_857"/> quarters.
                    Levies on whole turkeys were reduced from $0.0625 per kilogram to $0.04, and on
                    boned poultry from $0.125 to $0.075. Levies on other poultry products, including
                    turkey legs and thighs, remained unchanged. On October 18, the Commission left
                    unchanged export subsidies for poultry and eggs. (Telegram 4582 from Brussels,
                    February 8; Department of State, Central Files, INCO–POULTRY 17 <gloss
                        target="#t_EEC1">EEC</gloss>; telegram 9158 from Brussels, September 6;
                    ibid., INCO–POULTRY <gloss target="#t_EEC1">EEC</gloss>; and telegram 10060 from
                    Brussels, October 22; ibid.)</p>
            </div>
